ody":"In training phase, the call of `model.train()` is missed after the call of `sample()` and `eval()`.\r\n`model.train()` is only called at the start of each epoch. \r\nhttps://github.com/knazeri/edge-connect/blob/97338a2bcb243a774a84364e4686857b0c0d5618/src/edge_connect.py#L93  \r\nhttps://github.com/knazeri/edge-connect/blob/97338a2bcb243a774a84364e4686857b0c0d5618/src/edge_connect.py#L94     \r\nSo if `sample()` is called, the following training iterations are all under `eval()` model! Though there are no `dropout` or `batchNorm` layers in the network, the call of `train()` is still necessary to avoid some confusing bugs.     \r\n\r\n\r\nAnd I strongly recommend use `with torch.no_grad()` to wrap the validation or test phase, such as `sample()`, `eval()` or `test()` functions here, in order to save memory and speed up. Refer to [discuss about `no_grad()`](https://discuss.pytorch.org/t/model-eval-vs-with-torch-no-grad/19615/6)","closed_by":{"login":"youyuge34","id":15784256,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE1Nzg0MjU2","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/15784256?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/youyuge34","html_url":"https://github.com/youyuge34","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/youyuge34/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/youyuge34/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/youyuge34/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/youyuge34/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/youyuge34/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/youyuge34/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/youyuge34/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/youyuge34/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/youyuge34/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/knazeri/edge-connect/issues/9/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"